<subSubSection id="C30CE68AFFE2FF27FF4A8D81E58BFEBC" lastPageId="54" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA9B501FFE2FF22FF4A8D81E689FCB4" blockId="51.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FF4A8D81E61BFD6C" bold="true" box="[199,337,691,717]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FEE98D81E6EBFD6C" box="[356,417,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Head</emphasis>
dorsal surface smooth. 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FD368D86E450FD6C" box="[699,794,692,717]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Rostrum</emphasis>
broadly rounded triangular. 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FBE78D81E277FD6C" box="[1130,1341,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Interantennal lobe</emphasis>
slightly concave, lower corner larger than upper and right angled as opposed to wide angled upper corner. 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FB7E8DE5E2D6FD50" box="[1267,1436,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Accessory eyes</emphasis>
composed of 4 ommatidia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA9B501FFE2FF22FF4A8C2DE5B9FCFC" blockId="51.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FF4A8C2DE600FC98" box="[199,330,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Mouthparts</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FED48C2DE68FFC98" box="[345,453,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Maxilla 1</emphasis>
palp apex with 1 pointed lateral seta and 5 short, broad micro-dentate setal spines (observed, not illustrated). Mouthparts otherwise normal.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA9B501FFE2FF22FF4A8C55E4C0FBB3" blockId="51.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FF4A8C55E673FC20" box="[199,313,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Antenna 1</emphasis>
as long as pereonites 1–5 combined along dorsum, peduncle article 2 about 0.6 length of article 1, article 3 about 0.7 length of article 2, article 1 with 3 penicillate setae ventrally and two middorsally; 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FB548CB9E209FC04" box="[1241,1347,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">flagellum</emphasis>
slightly longer than peduncle, of 8+ articles; 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FDA38C82E447FC68" box="[558,781,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">accessory flagellum</emphasis>
of 4 articles. 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FC2E8C9DE35EFC68" box="[931,1044,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Antenna 2</emphasis>
slightly longer than pereonites 1–7 combined along dorsum, peduncular article 4 the longest; 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FC938CE1E4C2FC4C" box="[798,904,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">flagellum</emphasis>
of 6+ articles, most articles with single slender, curved robust seta dorsodistally; antenna otherwise sparsely setose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA9B501FFE2FF22FF4A8B29E353FB94" blockId="51.[151,1437,259,2014]" box="[199,1049,1051,1078]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FF4A8B29E61EFB94" box="[199,340,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Coxal plates</emphasis>
1–4 distally fringed with several long setae, otherwise smooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA9B501FFE2FF22FF4A8B0DE612FAD8" blockId="51.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FF4A8B0DE62FFBF8" box="[199,357,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Gnathopods 1</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FE118B0DE6E0FBF8" box="[412,426,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">2</emphasis>
of subequal length. 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FD038B0DE428FBF8" box="[654,866,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Gnathopod 1 basis</emphasis>
with several long and a few short setae posteriorly and a few long and short setae on anterior margin, 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FD468B56E445FBDC" box="[715,783,1124,1149]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">merus</emphasis>
with simple long and short setae on posterior margin, 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FAE38B56E7F4FB00" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">carpus</emphasis>
with a few long setae on anterior margin, posterior margin with about 8 groups of long and shorter setae, mostly finely pectinate setae, 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FE1F8B99E6B1FB64" box="[402,507,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">propodus</emphasis>
with a row of 5 stout pectinate setae on posterior margin, 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FB048B99E3ACFB64" box="[1161,1254,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">dactylus</emphasis>
with unguis 1/2 length of propodus, nearly straight. 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FDAF8BFDE5BEFB48" box="[546,756,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Gnathopod 2 basis</emphasis>
with few unequally long setae on anterior margin, and row of longer setae on distal half of posterior margin, 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FD2F8BC6E5ACFAAC" box="[674,742,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">merus</emphasis>
posterior margin with 3 strong, robust setae and 1 or 2 simple setae between the anterior 2 robust setae, 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FDE98A2AE5FAFA90" box="[612,688,1304,1329]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">carpus</emphasis>
with a few long setae on distal margin, posterior margin with about 8 groups of long and shorter setae, 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FDA88A09E5C4FAF4" box="[549,654,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">propodus</emphasis>
with long, simple setae on anterior margin and a few simple setae on posterior margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA9B501FFE2FF22FF4A8AB1E636FA63" blockId="51.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FF4A8AB1E625FA3C" box="[199,367,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Pereopods 3–4</emphasis>
basis, ischium, merus and carpus with a few simple marginal setae, propodus with stout anteroterminal robust seta.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA9B501FFE2FF22FF4A8AF9E252F8EC" blockId="51.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FF4A8AF9E601FA47" box="[199,331,1483,1510]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Pereopod 5</emphasis>
basis posterior margin straight, posterodistally with moderately extended rounded lobe, anterior margin with a few long simple setae proximally and some tiny setae more distally, 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FBDA8ADDE3E4F9A8" box="[1111,1198,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">ischium</emphasis>
and merus with few small simple setae, 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FEE28926E6F9F98C" box="[367,435,1556,1581]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">merus</emphasis>
with long robust seta posterodistally and tiny robust seta anterodistally, 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FB5D8926E256F98C" box="[1232,1308,1556,1581]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">carpus</emphasis>
with single robust seta posterodistally and row of 3 robust setae in anterodistal margin, 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FC6F8905E301F9F0" box="[994,1099,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">propodus</emphasis>
with 3 robust setae of varying length posterodistally. 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FE1E8969E559F9D4" box="[403,531,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Pereopod 6</emphasis>
basis narrow ovoid with shallow posterodistal lobe, anterior margin with long setae and a few short ones, remaining articles as in pereopod 5 with a few more setae. 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FBB0894DE3F7F93B" box="[1085,1213,1663,1690]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Pereopod 7</emphasis>
basis much broader than in 5 and 6, with large, broadly rounded posteroproximal lobe, posterodistal corner rounded, hardly projecting, mid-medial surface with several long setae, anterior margin with short group of setae in middle and in distal corner, 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FF1A89D9E7A4F8A4" box="[151,238,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">ischium</emphasis>
anterior margin with distal tuft of long setae, 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FD6289DEE479F8A4" box="[751,819,1772,1797]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">merus</emphasis>
as in pereopod 6 with a few more small anterior robust setae, 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FF538822E660F888" box="[222,298,1808,1833]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">carpus</emphasis>
longer than in pereopods 5 and 6 relative to propodus, posterior margin with single robust setae distally, anterior margin as in pereopod 6 but more spaced robust setae, 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FC178801E349F8EC" box="[922,1027,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">propodus</emphasis>
as in pereopods 5 and 6.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA9B501FFE2FF25FF4A8865E2CEFF74" blockId="51.[151,1437,259,2014]" lastBlockId="52.[151,1436,150,213]" lastPageId="52" lastPageNumber="53" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FF4A8865E67BF8D0" box="[199,305,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Uropod 1</emphasis>
peduncle reaching to end of peduncle of uropod 2, rami of equal length, about 2/3 length of peduncle, overreaching rami of uropod 2 with about 1/3 their length. 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FC938849E4C2F834" box="[798,904,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Uropod 2</emphasis>
rami reaching to about 1/3 along uropod 3 outer ramus, inner ramus slightly longer than outer ramus. 
<emphasis id="B9626913FFE2FF22FD7588ADE42FF818" box="[760,869,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Uropod 3</emphasis>
peduncle slightly more than half as long as outer ramus, rami elongate oval, reaching beyond apex of telson, outer ramus basal article with row of 9 robust setae dorsally, and 4 small robust setae ventrally, small second article with 3 dorsal robust setae; inner ramus as long as 4/5 of basal article of outer ramus, dorsal margin with row of long setae and 2 robust setae, apex with 3 robust setae.
</paragraph>
